7 An Act relating to Alzheimer’s disease and related
dementias; creating the Office of Alzheimer’s Disease
8 and Related Dementia Service Coordination within the
State Department of Health; providing powers and
9 duties; establishing dementia services coordinator
position; creating the Alzheimer’s Disease and
10 Related Dementia Service Coordination Revolving Fund;
specifying type of fund and source of monies; stating
11 purpose of fund; providing for expenditure of monies;
repealing 63 O.S. 2021, Sections 1-879.2 and 1-879.3,
12 which relate to Alzheimer’s disease and related
dementias; providing for codification; and providing
13 an effective date.
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-879.5 of Title 63, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. Subject to availability of funding, there is hereby created
20 within the State Department of Health the Office of Alzheimer’s
21 Disease and Related Dementia Service Coordination for the purpose of
22 providing statewide coordination, service system development, and
23 information on education, support, and other available services for
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1428 Page 1

1 indi viduals with Alzheimer’s disease or related dementias and their
2 caregivers.
3 B. The Office of Alzheimer’s Disease and Related Dementia
4 Service Coordination shall have the power and duty to:
5 1. Evaluate the coordination of dementia services within this
6 state and identify any duplicated services;
7 2. Coordinate informational resources affecting individuals
8 with Alzheimer’s disease or related dementias and their caregivers.
9 Such coordination shall include, but not be limited to:
10 a. using dementia-related data to coordinate strategies
11 designed to improve public health outcomes and service
12 delivery for individuals with Alzheimer’s disease or
13 related dementias and their caregivers,
14 b. establishing and maintaining relationships with other
15 state agencies, providers, organizations, and
16 community stakeholders to meet the needs of affected
17 populations and prevent the duplication of services,
18 c. supporting the provision of dementia-specific staff
19 training across all relevant state agencies and
20 organizations, and
21 d. recommending strategies to improve coordination of
22 dementia-related services and resources provided by
23 public and private entities;
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1428 Page 2

1 3. Streamline all applicable state government services to
2 increase efficiency and improve the quality of dementia-related care
3 in residential, home-based, and community-based settings;
4 4. Identify grant opportunities to expand the scope of services
5 for individuals with Alzheimer’s disease or related dementias and
6 their caregivers and apply for the grant opportunities;
7 5. Perform other duties relevant to supporting policy
8 development and implementation to enhance the quality of life for
9 individuals with Alzheimer’s disease or related dementias and their
10 caregivers;
11 6. Promote public and professional awareness and education
12 related to Alzheimer’s disease and related dementias and access to
13 needed services and programs; and
14 7. Collect and monitor data concerning the impact of
15 Alzheimer’s disease and related dementias in this state.
16 C. Subject to availability of funding, the Office of
17 Alzheimer’s Disease and Related Dementia Service Coordination shall
18 maintain on staff at least one dementia services coordinator. The
19 dementia services coordinator shall be a full-time, permanent
20 employee and shall be responsible for the staffing and operational
21 details of the Office.
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-879.6 of Title 63, unless
24 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1428 Page 3

1 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
2 for the State Department of Health to be designated the “Alzheimer’s
3 Disease and Related Dementia Service Coordination Revolving Fund”.
4 The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year
5 limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
6 Department from grants, gifts, and donations provided for the
7 purpose of funding the Office of Alzheimer’s Disease and Related
8 Dementia Service Coordination created under Section 1 of this act.
9 All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
10 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Department for
11 the purpose provided for in this section. Expenditures from the
12 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
13 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
14 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
15 payment.
16 SECTION 3. REPEALER 63 O.S. 2021, Sections 1-879.2 and
17 1-879.3, are hereby repealed.
18 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
